<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="461" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5931/462.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">de Billier</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-07-22"><hi rend="italic">July 22,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Says the British minister on behalf of British Government has recognized
                            the new Shah of Persia on July 21 and asks if he may recognize
                            Government.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>